    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-01-07T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-01-07T06:00:00-05:00" n="583"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d583">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.24/1234b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Second Secretary of Embassy in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thompson</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="28" xml:id="d583fn28">Llewellyn E. Thompson, Jr., Second
                        Secretary of Embassy and Consul in the Soviet Union, was in charge of the
                        group remaining in Moscow after the removal of the Embassy to
                        Kuibyshev.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-01-07T07:00:00-04:00"
                            >January 7, 1943—7 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>12. From Stettinius<note n="29" xml:id="d583fn29">Edward R. Stettinius, Jr.,
                        Lend-Lease Administrator.</note> to Faymonville.<note n="30"
                        xml:id="d583fn30">Brig. Gen. Philip R. Faymonville, head of the United
                        States Supply Mission in the Soviet Union; Lend-Lease Representative.</note>
                    We have informed Litvinov<note n="31" xml:id="d583fn31">Maxim Maximovich
                        Litvinov, Soviet Ambassador in the United States.</note> that the time is at
                    hand to initiate the Third Protocol. Soviet requirements for the period July 1,
                    1943 to June 30, 1944 are desired. Presentation of these should be grouped to
                    correspond as nearly as <pb facs="0750" n="738" xml:id="pg_738"/> possible to
                    the Second Protocol categories. Planning here will be aided by promptness in as
                    much as production schedules are now being set up well in advance. Alloy steel
                    requirements are especially urgent. [Stettinius.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
